@node "Introduction" "Introduction"

                       @{b}@{u}Introduction@{ub}@{uu}


These are some usefull, at least for me! :-) scripts for the Thor message
system.

Currently the suite is made by the following scripts, developed and tested on
Thor v2.6.


     @{"GMAutoWrite" link "GMAutoWrite.guide/main" 0} will automatically create email events at specified
                 intervals: either every N days or every day N!

     @{"GMSignature" link "GMSignature.guide/main" 0} will let you add an external file as message signature and
                 execute an external program to create the tag!

     @{"GMCleanConf" link "GMCleanConf.guide/main" 0} is an enhancement to BBSREAD arexx cmd @{"PackDataFile" link "BBSReadRexx.guide/packdatafile" 0}: before
                 executing it messages can be saved to disk with a @{i}nice@{ui}
                 filename and a @{i}nice@{ui} header using @{"GMarchive" link "GMarchive.guide/main" 0}! :-) Selection
                 is done by month and year.

     @{"GMarchive" link "GMarchive.guide/main" 0}   I wasn't satisfied of the currently available message
                 saving scripts so I've wrote mine and I've wrote it to
                 allow use from both Thor's ARexx menu and from another
                 script.


Of course they need to be correctly @{"installed" link "Installation" 0} and configured before you can
use them. For the configuration please see their respective documentation.
@endnode

@node "Installation" "Installation"

                            @{b}@{u}Installation@{ub}@{uu}


Simply copy the following directories in the right place!

1) Copy @{i}Docs@{ui} to <ThorPath>/Docs

2) Copy @{i}Rexx@{ui} to <ThorPath>/rexx

3) Copy @{i}envarc@{ui} to both Env: and EnvArc:

4) Create/Modify the configuration files in Env: and EnvArc: as needed
   Currently:
     Thor/@{"GMAutoWrite.cfg" link "GMAutoWrite.guide/configuration" 0}
     Thor/@{"Internet_S.cfg" link "GMSignature.guide/configuration" 0} (it must be renamed to your System name!)
     Thor/@{"Internet_C.cfg" link "GMCleanConf.guide/configuration" 0} (it must be renamed to your System name!)


<ThorPath> is the directory containing Thor itself.
@endnode

